If you’re craving expensive but very flavorful and prime quality tacos this is the place to go. Yes, each taco set (x2) is average $14 but is truly worth it. Order all of them, pork, beef and chicken (even mushroom) surprisingly very different flavors and textures, rich meat and good salsas, perfect toppings -onion, cilantro, pinapple and traditional Mexican condiments with Mexican abuela corn tortillas. Looking forward to come back and try more items of the menu.  Great service, everyone was super friendly and genuinely happy of interacting with customers  Follow @destination_food33 for more reviews
Good, drinks and service are always good, unfortunately a reduced menu due to Covid but still worth a visit. Note margaritas are the best I have had in NYC
Great tacos
Great mushrooms veggie tacos very flavorable. Chips and Guac are recommended! The frozen strawberry margarita 😉

Very authentic cuisine from Oaxaca. Tacos come 2 per order and are very flavorful. The aguachile pack a punch with the serrano peppers and come with scallops. The equites off the cob is for 2 and is generous. My favorite taco was a barbacoa. The menu is great for sharing!
Just wow.
This restaurant is overpriced, and the food is very small. The bartender didn't put enough alcohol in our Margarita. We had to drink the most expensive lemonade in Williamsburg.
The tacos were just okay for me. But what I would give 5 stars to is that triple chocolate cake. Delicious!! So good I had to get it twice
Spicy and pricy.

Outstanding food accompanied by great service. We were a large group, all drinks where brought out at the same time. We all received our food at their same time and not one dish was luke warm all dishes where nice and hot. I must mention that the bartender (Mario) really know how miss drinks.
Delicious food, unique tasty sauces, great drinks, and friendly service!
Really good food.  Huge space.  Great for family brunch.

This is one of my regular spots. I moved in right across the street a couple years ago and was happy to find a great restaurant with an awesome vibe just steps away. In addition to their great food, the mezcal and tequila options are pretty amazing. Definitely recommend this place to any fan of mexican food!
Great restaurant. Awesome vibes. Delicious food. Fast service. Just a lovely experience all-around.

I highly recommend this restaurant. The food is high quality, and we enjoyed the ambiance. They have good menu options for happy hour too. Try the esquites and flor de calabaza tacos.

An awesome atmosphere with a simple but solid menu! I got the steak tacos this time but definitely look forward to making my way back to try the others. The prices definitely reflect the quality of the food & the service was very friendly! Possibly one of my new favorite bars in the area!
Nice place with a relaxed vibe and some pretty good food to boot. The guacamole in particular was top-end, as was the ceviche.

Tuna Tostada and Hibiscus margarita are one of my favorites on this Mexican spot in Brooklyn. Please don’t hesitate with the fish tacos and aguachile; interesting happy hour.
Come here at happy hour - great (relatively) cheap margaritas, delicious Caso Fundido and relaxed atmosphere.

Beautiful bar and sunny interior. Tasty salsas and delicious cocktails. Also, I had the blistered shishito peppers, and their's we're about the most delicious ones I have ever had. Final note, Katie Holmes and Suri Cruise came in as I was leaving, and another actress I recognized but don't know the name of was at the bar.

Overdosed on the most delicious tacos. The mouthwatering guac was gone before I even had a chance to photograph it! Even my most picky-eater friend loves it here - for a very good reason. The service was also absolutely top notch. Thanks so much for a great meal guys!

Amazing. Came here in October, the weather was so beautiful and we were able to sit at the open window and do some people watching. This restaurant does not shy away from spicy, so beware. Everything was extra delicious. The appetizers, guacamole, col de bruselas, and chiles toreados were all outstanding. We both had the fish tacos as a main, and left stuffed. The classic margaritas had us leaving much happier than we arrived.

Very good cocktails but the food isn't as good as expected. We ordered the shrimp ceviche, queso fundido, carnitas tacos, and carne asada tacos. The tacos lacked flavor but the appetizers were good.

You know how, once a particular flight gets delayed, the airline would rather continue to heap delays on that flight than allow multiple other flights to get delayed so they can say 90% of their flights are on time?  That’s pretty much how our dinner went, one gaffe after another while the tables around us had no problems.  Made for a lousy experience and the food wasn’t strong enough to redeem it, especially the rubbery and dry queso fundido. (FWIW, the rest was good, though overpriced.)  The coup de grace was being brought a round of drinks and thinking, ok, thanks for acknowledging the missteps, only to have it turn out be yet another mistake—they were for a different table.  Sigh.

Loud as hell. Forget about quiet conversation. But their guacamole and chips are to die for. Made to order and fresh, not made in batches.   Crunchy and thick house made chips.  Amazing beef tacos. Tender and high quality. Salad was fresh with the right amount of various ingredients in every bite. You can tell they put a lot of care and attention to detail in each dish.  This will be my goto place once they work out the kinks since they're newly opened. The food took way too long to prepare. Fix that and you've earned  the 5 stars.

This place is really hard to get ahold of. I have called numerous times during business hours to no avail and the voicemail is not set up. Open table doesn't take large reservations so really not sure how to reserve tables for bigger parties? Also there is no email provided on the site, so there is literally no way to make a reservation.
great new mexican spot in the neighborhood, slightly upscale
The vegetarian tacos!! The best. The salad and the flan, also amazing. So happy to have this place in the hood!

We waited for more than an hour, only to get seated and learn that 1/4 of the menu (tacos) were finished. After we ordered and got our food they told us they had run out of tortillas, so no tortillas for the queso fundido we'd allready ordered. At the end the GM presented herself and take care of the check for us; very nice gesture but we won't be coming back. Food is good but many more and better Mexican restaurants out there.
Happened to walk by on their second day being open. From the drinks to the aesthetic I'm excited about the addition to the neighborhood.
